{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PointMesh"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Mesh with a single Point primitive."}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PointMesh","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The PointMesh is made from a single point. Instead of relying on triangles, points are rendered as a single rectangle on the screen with a constant size. They are intended to be used with Particle systems, but can be used as a cheap way to render constant size billboarded sprites (for example in a point cloud).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"PointMeshes, must be used with a material that has a point size. Point size can be accessed in a shader with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"POINT_SIZE"},{"type":"text","text":", or in a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BaseMaterial3D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" by setting "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BaseMaterial3D\/usePointSize"},{"text":" and the variable ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BaseMaterial3D\/pointSize","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using PointMeshes, properties that normally alter vertices will be ignored, including billboard mode, grow, and cull face."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/document